  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Holocaust in Contemporary Education European Curricula, Textbooks and Pupils&apos; Perceptions in Comparison</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is a joint initiative of UNESCO and the Georg Eckert Institute for Textbook Research. It is designed to provide a comprehensive overview of current evolutions in the field of Holocaust education, in the context of countries most directly affected by it, through a comparative analysis of curricula, textbooks and pupils perceptions of the Holocaust and to ensure, at a global scale, guidance for education stakeholders wishing to strengthen capacity to teach about this subject.</narrative>
  </description>
